  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\n\nthe native ens registration flow checks the addr and not the owner of the ens name\n\n#### Expected behavior\n\nit should check if the owner is the user wallet, otherwise he can't make a transaction to change the pubkey for instance because he doesn't own the name, even if the addr is his.\n\nthis means that we probably need a few extra flows for the following cases:\n- user is owner, addr is not his: need to set addr\n- user is owner, addr is not his and pubkey is not his: need to set addr and pubkey\n- user is not owner but addr and pubkey are his: allow to add username but warn user that if he doesn't have control over owning address, he will get his identity and funds stolen\n\n#### Actual behavior\n\nowner is ignored and only addr is checked\n\n#### Notes\n\nnot a priority because you need to manage names outside of status to get these situations",
